HEADWORD: glorified
<hw>glorified</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>accorded sacrosanct
or authoritative standing.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> canonized.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Made to appear more important or better than it
actually is; <as>as, The Chief Financial Officer was little more than a
<ex>glorified</ex> accountant</as>.</def> ⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glorify</ent>⟦br⟧
